title: What channel is Kansas City Royals-Toronto Blue Jays on? TV, live stream for ALCS Game 1
text:
Kansas City will host Toronto in Game 1 of the American League Championship Series on Friday night.
Marco Estrada will get the start for Toronto and will be opposed by Kansas City's Edinson Volquez.
The game starts at 7:30 p.m. and will be televised by Fox.
Here's how to catch Fox in Central New York:
Time Warner: Channel 1206 (SD & HD) and channel 8 for non-digital customers Verizon Fios: Channel 508 (HD) and 8 (SD) DirectTV: Channel 68 (SD & HD) Dish Network: Channel 68 (SD &HD) New Visions: Channel 608 (HD) and 8 (SD) You can also watch online or through tablets and mobile devices using FOX Sports GO .
